---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Contribute to How to Law"
  description="Learn how to collaborate on lessons, diagrams, and quizzes for the How to Law project."
  noIndex
>
  <section class="bg-background">
    <div class="mx-auto flex max-w-4xl flex-col gap-10 px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <header class="space-y-4">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-accent">Help it grow</p>
        <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-foreground sm:text-4xl">Join the writing room</h1>
        <p class="text-base text-foreground/80">
          Every page here was drafted, reviewed, and polished by community members. Whether you love outlining doctrine, sketching visual aids, or writing practice questions, there is room for your voice.
        </p>
      </header>
      <article class="space-y-6 rounded-3xl border border-border bg-card/80 p-6 shadow-subtle">
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-3 sm:flex-row sm:items-center sm:justify-between">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">Start with the style highlights</h2>
          <a
            href="/how-to-law/docs/STYLE_GUIDE.md"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-accent px-4 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-accent-foreground shadow-subtle transition hover:opacity-95 focus:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-accent"
          >
            Read the style guide
          </a>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-foreground/80">
          The style guide covers voice, formatting, and accessibility patterns that keep lessons consistent. Skim it before you open a pull request so your edits slide smoothly into review.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="grid gap-6 rounded-3xl border border-border bg-card/70 p-6 shadow-subtle lg:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">Topics we are eager to add</h2>
          <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm text-foreground/80">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="mt-1 inline-flex h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-accent" aria-hidden="true" />
              Trial mechanics: voir dire, evidentiary objections, and jury instructions for the USAR setting.
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="mt-1 inline-flex h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-accent" aria-hidden="true" />
              Administrative and agency law basics for in-universe regulatory bodies.
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="mt-1 inline-flex h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-accent" aria-hidden="true" />
              Appellate practice beyond the Supreme Court module, including standards of review and briefing tips.
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="mt-1 inline-flex h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-accent" aria-hidden="true" />
              Scenario-based exercises that blend criminal procedure with constitutional issues.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">Lesson frontmatter checklist</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-foreground/80">
            New lessons live in the <code>src/content/classroom</code> collection. Copy an existing entry and update the frontmatter fields below before you write:
          </p>
          <pre class="overflow-x-auto rounded-2xl bg-background/90 p-4 text-xs text-foreground/90"><code>---
title: &quot;Your Lesson Title&quot;
module: module-id
lesson: 3
summary: &quot;One-sentence hook for the lesson.&quot;
objectives:
  - &quot;Learners will be able to...&quot;
references:
  - label: &quot;Statute or case name&quot;
    cite: &quot;123 U.S. 456&quot;
quizId: your-quiz-slug
---</code></pre>
          <p class="text-xs text-foreground/70">
            Keep filenames kebab-cased, increment the <code>lesson</code> order, and update the module index if you add or remove lessons.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>
      <article class="grid gap-6 rounded-3xl border border-border bg-card/80 p-6 shadow-subtle lg:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">Diagrams and process flows</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-foreground/80">
            Sketch your idea in Markdown or share a link to a collaborative design file. Call out the story beats, labels, and citations each panel should include. Reviewers can help convert the concept into accessible SVGs that match the site palette.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-foreground/80">
            When you open the pull request, attach alt-text in the description and note any animation needs so we can test for reduced-motion settings.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">Quizzes and knowledge checks</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-foreground/80">
            Draft three to five multiple-choice questions per lesson with answer rationales. Flag which objective each question reinforces. Store them in <code>src/content/quizzes</code> and reuse existing data structures for scoring so progress stays in each learnerâ€™s browser.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-foreground/80">
            If you are unsure how to format the schema, open an issue or draft PR with one example question and we will pair with you to finish the set.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>
      <article class="rounded-3xl border border-border bg-background/70 p-6 shadow-subtle">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">Pull request etiquette</h2>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm text-foreground/80">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="mt-1 inline-flex h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-accent" aria-hidden="true" />
            Start with a draft PR when you want early feedback. Summarize what is complete and where you need eyes.
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="mt-1 inline-flex h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-accent" aria-hidden="true" />
            Keep commits scoped and descriptive. Screenshots or GIFs are helpful when you update visuals.
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="mt-1 inline-flex h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-accent" aria-hidden="true" />
            Tag reviewers who know the module you are editing, respond to feedback with context, and celebrate new contributors.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
